definitions.definition: To bring in a harvest; reap ; glean .
examples: We harvested the apples in September already.

definitions.definition: To take a living organism as part of a managed process to gather food or resources, often with the intention of maintaining a healthy population.
examples: An efficient rifle or shotgun can harvest a deer for venison.

definitions.definition: To be occupied bringing in a harvest.
examples: We're going to harvest day and night, because the weather is about to turn sour.
The rising star harvested well-deserved acclaim, even an Oscar under 21.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To bring in a harvest; reap ; glean .
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To take a living organism as part of a managed process to gather food or resources, often with the intention of maintaining a healthy population.
( intransitive ) To be occupied bringing in a harvest.
( transitive ) To win , achieve a gain .
